ContentDesc_Prophetie - Zeromus: 'Twas only when the Ascians' god was brought low, its remnants dispersed into aether, that Golbez could piece together his plan. In the red moon's answer to the Cradle of Darkness did he use that aether to birth the dread voidsent Zeromus, which, driven by Azdaja's longing to return home, is now poised to break the barrier between worlds. And so the Warrior of Light stands fast against the Darkness, a flickering beacon of hope. Should they fail, the Thirteenth's deliverance will prove the Source's destruction.
Instancecontenttextdata_38001_Text: O stifled Darkness in moon abiding...
Instancecontenttextdata_38003_Text: My Darkness shall devour all Light.
Instancecontenttextdata_38007_Text: Beyond the veil my home doth lie...
Instancecontenttextdata_38010_Text: I wish but to return home.
Instancecontenttextdata_38011_Text: In my memory the stars yet shine, attending the moon...
Instancecontenttextdata_38012_Text: Bright as stars in the night.
Instancecontenttextdata_38013_Text: Her will...my will...shall not be denied.
Instancecontenttextdata_38015_Text: By my power shall all know salvation!
Instancecontenttextdata_38016_Text: To the last you would deny my heart's desire...
Instancecontenttextdata_38017_Text: Your flesh shall melt and seethe!
Instancecontenttextdata_38023_Text: All are as one in Darkness.
Instancecontenttextdata_38029_Text: Oh, to look upon such splendor once more...
Instancecontenttextdata_38030_Text: Return to me, my beloved star!
Instancecontenttextdata_38031_Text: All who oppose me shall be consigned to nothingness.
Instancecontenttextdata_38032_Text: In endless Dark embrace your end.
